>> ssh -p <port> <hostname> -l <user>

ssh into the hostname on <port> and as <user>. Password is asked upon login.

>> ssh -p <port> <hostname> -l <user> -i <ssh key>

ssh as above, using the ssh-key instead of a password.

>> ssh -p <port> <hostname> -l <user> <command>

ssh and execute the given command.

